<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE PHOTO CONTEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"Classics," The Times' 16th annual photography contest (May 28), asked for 
photos that captured the Southern California image. Top honors went to pictures 
of a garden hose in someone's back yard, a rock enveloped in surrealistic 
colors and the sun trying to peep through the smoke of a brush fire. Where do 
these judges live, on the moon? Yes, we have brush fires, yes, we have garden 
hoses by the mile, but surely, our image could have been better represented by 
more identifiable pictures. 
</P>
<P>
RICHARD R. ROGERS 
</P>
<P>
Sierre Madre 
