<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIXON ON U.S. CHINA POLICY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Thanks for your in-depth coverage on China (June 25). The case of a 
gerontocracy turned "gerontocrazy" reminds me of the ancient Roman Senate, 
so-called for being made of "senes" or senescent members. A graphic Latin 
saying characterizes that citadel of power for all ages and cultures: 
"Senatores, boni viri; senatus, mala bestia" (The senators, decent guys; the 
senate, a wild beast.) 
</P>
<P>
MARY C. GARIANO 
</P>
<P>
Northridge 
</P>
