<TEXT>
<P>
Barratt Irvine, a division of home builder Barratt American, has named Stefan 
Markowitz president. In his new post, Markowitz will oversee the development, 
construction and marketing of the division's projects in Orange, San Bernardino 
and north Riverside counties. He will be working out of the Irvine office. 
</P>
<P>
Ted Peterson, vice president of Asset Management Group in the San Diego area, a 
division of Collins Development Co. and La Jolla Development Co., has been made 
a partner in Collins Development. Peterson is responsible for retail leasing 
operations with Asset Management Group, which handles the property management 
and leasing of commercial and retail properties for the other companies. 
</P>
<P>
Hopkins Development Co., a specialist in shopping center redevelopment, has 
added John Withers to its staff as senior vice president of residential 
development. He will oversee the residential part of the firm's mixed-use 
projects, act as a liaison with contracted developers and evaluate residential 
components of existing properties. The Newport Beach-based company has sites in 
La Mirada, San Ramon, Laguna Beach and San Francisco. 
</P>
<P>
Michael Koss, chairman and chief executive officer of Koss Financial Corp. in 
Los Angeles, has been elected to the board of directors of the Business 
Property Council of Los Angeles. The organization has been created to represent 
the commercial real estate industry and to promote careful planning of 
development. 
</P>
<P>
Kathleen Dantagnan has joined Urban West Communities as vice president of 
marketing and sales. She will be responsible for all aspects of marketing and 
sales in the company's regional offices. Dantagnan will also be in charge of 
product design, interior design, public relations, and escrow and loan 
functions. 
</P>
<P>
Watson Land Co. has announced the promotion of Pilar Perry to vice president of 
public affairs. She will handle the company's role in civic activities. Watson 
is a major developer of industrial centers in Los Angeles County. 
</P>
<P>
Deyo P. Breen has been named vice president of operations for the Inland Empire 
division of Calprop Corp. Breen will be in charge of all of Calprop's 
activities, including land acquisition and construction. 
</P>
<P>
Arthur D. Aston Jr. has been appointed executive vice president and corporate 
secretary of the American Industrial Real Estate Assn. The 1,200-member 
organization represents more than 150 industrial real estate offices in the 
Southern California area. 
</P>
<P>
The Los Angeles County Board of Supervisors has appointed Judith Hane Leimert 
to the Los Angeles County Child Care Advisory Board. Leimert, senior vice 
president and general counsel of Watt Industries, is the only real estate 
developer on the 19-member advisory board of business and civic leaders. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
ACCOLADES: Paul E. Griffin Jr., president and chief executive officer of 
Griffin Homes, has received the Edward A. Dickson Alumnus of the Year 
Achievement Award for his longtime volunteer and philanthropic efforts on the 
university's behalf. This award is the highest honor bestowed by the UCLA 
Alumni Assn. 
</P>
<P>
</P>
<P>
Architects 
</P>
<P>
Howard F. Thompson Associates Inc., a Newport Beach-based architecture, land 
planning and interior design firm, has announced four promotions to the post of 
senior associate: John S. Delacy, project manager; Sohrab Charna, project 
manager; Daniela Bogdan-Kennedy, director of planning coordination, and Leonard 
Malmquist, director of design. 
</P>
<P>
Glenda Young has joined Los Angeles- and Montclair-based CHCG Architects as 
manager of marketing. Her duties will include coordinating the firm's business 
development, client services and public relations. CHCG specializes in 
corporate, educational, public, industrial and health-care facilities 
throughout the Southland. 
</P>
<P>
Mark Handler has been named senior project manager at Knitter &amp; Associates 
in Newport Beach. Handler has developed expertise over the past 12 years in 
attached housing and land planning. 
</P>
<P>
Edward Carson Beall &amp; Associates, a Torrance-based architectural and 
interior design firm, has appointed Won Na Ng to project architect. She will be 
responsible for the design and development of custom single-family homes and 
remodels, from initial conception to completion. 
</P>
<P>
Gordon, Friedman, Baldwinson, Associates has announced four new project 
directors: Marc Dubin, Ron McMaster, George Levinthal and Richard Fletcher. The 
Encino-based firm focuses on retail and mixed-use projects. 
