<HEADLINE>
<P>
MAGAZINE HONORS CLAREMONT STUDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Edward Tessier of Claremont has been named one of 20 winners of the 1989 Time 
magazine College Achievement Award. 
</P>
<P>
Tessier, a junior at Pomona College and a quadriplegic, was honored for 
community service, including forming a Panel for Architectural Review to ensure 
that all campus building projects are accessible to the disabled and for 
organizing handicap awareness groups for student leaders. 
</P>
<P>
The award includes a $3,000 scholarship. 
</P>
</TEXT>
