<P>
BOY, 7, IN GOOD CONDITION AFTER FALLING INTO POOL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A 7-year-old boy who was discovered unconscious on the bottom of a swimming 
pool was in good condition Saturday at Childrens Hospital of Los Angeles, a 
spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
Abdullahim Muhammed, who is from Nigeria, was last seen by his parents Ibrahim 
and Amina about 2:30 p.m. Friday at their home in the 11600 block of Burbank 
Boulevard in North Hollywood, Los Angeles police said. He was discovered at the 
bottom of a nearby apartment house pool by registered nurse John Silkey just 
before 3:30 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
Silkey resuscitated the boy and called paramedics. 
</P>
<P>
The boy's parents did not report their son missing until 9:30 p.m., after their 
own search was unsuccessful. 
</P>
