<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE: NUGGET SALE TALKS IN PROGRESS -- $65 MILLION? 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Denver Post reported that the Denver Nuggets have been sold to a group of 
Chicago investors for $65 million, but team owner Sidney Shlenker said 
negotiations are still in progress and no deal had yet been made. 
</P>
<P>
"I'm still the owner so far," Shlenker said. "We are in conversation. I expect 
for something to be announced in the next few days. It's a little premature." 
</P>
<P>
Shlenker, who is shifting his business operations top Memphis, didn't identify 
the investors but said the Nuggets would remain in Denver. 
</P>
</TEXT>
