<HEADLINE>
<P>
NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Guard Michael Jordan of the Chicago Bulls was ticketed while traveling on 
Interstate 75 near Lexington, Ky., June 6 for going 90 m.p.h. in a 60-m.p.h. 
zone. 
</P>
<P>
When Jordan failed to appear in Fayette County District Court Thursday, Judge 
John Adams issued a warrant for his arrest. 
</P>
<P>
Lexington patrolman Tommy Puckett, who stopped Jordan, also cited the 
basketball player for failing to have an operator's license. Puckett said 
Jordan was en route from his home in Highland Park, Ill., to his house in North 
Carolina. 
