NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rose's Record charged between horses in the stretch to win the $149,200 Chicago 
Budweiser Breeders' Cup at Arlington International Racecourse in Arlington 
Heights, Ill. 
</P>
<P>
Ridden by Jorge Velasquez, Rose's Record paid $11 to win and was timed in 1:24 
3/5 while earning $93,120 for owners David and Nancy Ringler of Laguna Hills, 
Calif. Sunshine Always was second, Daloma third. 
</P>
