NEWSWIRE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Cleveland Crunch expansion team selected a 24-year-old heart transplant 
recipient, Simon Keith, as the top pick in the first round of the Major Indoor 
Soccer League's college draft. 
</P>
<P>
Keith, of Victoria, Canada, was a forward for Nevada Las Vegas and has been 
playing in the Canadian Soccer League for the Victoria Vistas. He received a 
heart transplant in 1987 from a 17-year-old English soccer player who died of a 
cerebral brain clot during a match. 
</P>
